Kenya Reinsurance Rises on Plans for Shariah-Compliant Unit

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-06-13T12:47:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/kenya-reinsurance-rises-on-plans-for-shariah-compliant-unit.html
Kenya Reinsurance Corp. rose for a
second day after Business Daily reported the state-run reinsurer
plans to establish a Shariah-compliant unit.  The stock of Kenya Re, as the company is known, climbed 1.4
percent to 9.50 shillings by the 3 p.m. close in the capital,
Nairobi.  Kenya Re plans to tap into the expanding Islamic-finance
industry in  Africa  and the  Middle East , the Nairobi-based
newspaper reported today, citing Chief Executive Officer Jadiah
Mwarania. The company will also venture into micro-insurance and
political-risk insurance, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
